  "id": "5d8d55e4-5f6b-58c4-b942-6bae0a5d7a70",
  "slug": "pork-barbecue",
  "name": "Pork Barbecue",
  "recipe_type": "main",
  "brief_description": "Filipino skewered marinated pork slices that are grilled to perfection.",
  "cuisine": "Filipino",
  "instructions": [
    {
      "position": 1,
      "text": "Arrange pork slices in a large bowl. Add Knorr SavorRich, soy sauce, ketchup, sugar, garlic, and ground black pepper. Mix well. Cover and refrigerate for at least 3 hours. Note: marinating the meat longer will provide better results."
    },
    {
      "position": 2,
      "text": "Skewer the marinated meat on a bamboo skewer (also called barbecue stick). Set aside."
    },
    {
      "position": 3,
      "text": "Heat-up the grill. Start to grill the pork barbecue for 3 to 5 minutes per side. Continue this step until pork is thoroughly cooked. Note: baste with a mixture of soy sauce, banana ketchup, and vegetable oil after turning the barbecue over."
    },
    {
      "position": 4,
      "text": "Serve with warm rice and a dip of spicy vinegar. Enjoy!"
    }
  ],
